  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">FOCUS Nepal, Dhading - Earthquake Recovery Programme Nepal - Code 9</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Christian Aid through partners had responded as part of the rapid response actions in Gorkha, Dhading, Sindhupalchowk and Dolakha. The needs assessment has indicated that the affected communities continue to have needs of recovery and winterization in the immediate context, particularly in more remote VDCs which were difficult to access in inclement weather conditions including winter and monsoon. The areas identified of recovery actions include the following: 
&#x2022; Repair and rehabilitation of destroyed/ dysfunctional water schemes : Component 01 
&#x2022; Technical guidance for safer shelter and winterization provision: Component 02
&#x2022; Livelihoods recovery actions for sustainable development : Component 03
&#x2022; Education and DRR mainstreaming to ensure safer culture for future: Component 04 
&#x2022; Inclusive DRR actions and community participation : Component 05</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall GOAL of the programme is to achieve safe and secure shelter, food security, water sanitation and hygiene, and livelihoods for the most affected households in targeted VDCs in 3 heavily affected Districts of Nepal.</narrative>
  </description>
